[cite_start]**To draw a line parallel to the given line** [cite: 520]

[cite_start]**Construction (I): To draw a line parallel to the given line through a point outside the given line using set-square.** [cite: 521, 522]

[cite_start]**Construction (II): To draw a parallel line to a given line at a given distance.** [cite: 552, 553]
[cite_start]Method: Draw a line parallel to line l at a distance 2.5 cm. [cite: 554, 555]
1.  Draw line l. [cite_start]Take two points A and B on the line l. [cite: 557]
2.  [cite_start]Draw perpendiculars to the line l from points A and B. [cite: 565]
3.  [cite_start]On the perpendicular lines take points P and Q at a distance of 2.5cm from A and B respectively. [cite: 568]
4.  Draw line PQ. [cite_start]Line PQ is a line parallel to the line l at a distance 2.5cm. [cite: 569]

